The paper deals with formal models of learning from teachers, which is a topic commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper introduces a new model of teaching and establishes its optimality, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of certain decision problems, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), or discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
